** use case for the DIP Switches **
Leaving ports open/floating creates small interference in a sensitive ADC. Being a 24 bit adc the more stability the better.

*** Warning about DIP Switches **
The Input/Data is tied to GND, meaning if you do plug a sensor into a GND'd port you will damage the sensor
only use if your having really bad cross talk or interference
